sparql_query_raw:
 To create a SPARQL query for DBpedia based on the given context and entity mappings, we can translate the Wikidata properties and entities to their corresponding DBpedia equivalents.

Here is the translated SPARQL query for DBpedia:

```
<sparql>
SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Astronaut> [] .
  { ?uri <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/nationality> <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union> }
  UNION
  { ?uri <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/nationality> <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia> }
}
</sparql>
```

This query retrieves all entities that are classified as astronauts (`<http://dbpedia.org/ontology/Astronaut>`) and have a nationality of either the Soviet Union (`<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union>`) or Russia (`<http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia>`).
